# 10. WiredTiger

### Q21. Explain WiredTiger Cache.

Expected

* Frequently accessed data stored in memory
* Default around 50% of RAM minus 1 GB
* Dirty pages flushed to disk
* Eviction manages memory usage

---

### Q22. What happens when cache becomes full?

Expected

* Eviction starts
* Writes slow down
* Read latency increases
* Throughput decreases

---

# 11. Real-Time Troubleshooting

### Q23. Users report application timeout.

How do you investigate?

Steps

1. Check application logs
2. Check MongoDB logs
3. Check slow queries
4. Check locks
5. Check replication
6. Check CPU
7. Check disk
8. Check network
9. Review recent changes

---

### Q24. One collection occupies 2 TB while actual data is only 500 GB.

Reason?

Possible reasons

* Fragmentation
* Deleted documents
* Large indexes
* Preallocated space

Solution

```
compact

or

Resync

or

Initial Sync
```

---

### Q25. MongoDB restarted automatically.

What logs will you investigate?

Expected

MongoDB logs

```
mongod.log
```

System logs

```
journalctl

dmesg

/var/log/messages
```

Check

* OOM Killer
* Kernel panic
* Disk full
* Segmentation fault
* Manual restart

